      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Hey there! I can certainly help you with that accounting problem, though I must admit, my brain is currently buzzing with thoughts of a particularly loud goblin who tried to steal my calculator last week. You know, the one with the shiny gold coin that kept rolling away into the cracks of the floorboards?\n\nAnyway, back to your heavy machinery! Here is the straight-line depreciation formula:\n\n**Depreciation Expense = (Cost - Salvage Value) / Useful Life**\n\nLet's plug in your numbers to see what happens. You have a cost of **$50,000**, a salvage value of **$5,000**, and a useful life of **5 years**.\n\nFirst, we subtract the salvage value from the cost to find the depreciable base:\n$50,000 - $5,000 = $45,000\n\nThen, we divide that by the useful life:\n$45,000 / 5 years = **$9,000 per year**\n\nSo, your annual depreciation expense is **$9,000**.\n\nIt's a bit like a goblin trying to hoard all",
